\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {VII}{\ignorespaces Cross-model replication: embedding regret bias (37 models, 7 families; all batches combined). $d_\text  {DN}$/$d_\text  {CN}$: standardized effect size vs.\ neutral (mean difference divided by population SD of the pooled D$+$N distribution); 95\% CI from 1{,}000 bootstrap resamples. All 37 models show D$>$N ($d_\text  {DN}=0.42$--$1.86$); 36/37 show C$>$N with 95\% CI excluding zero ($d_\text  {CN}=0.07$--$2.10$; exception: GPT-5.4-mini $d_\text  {CN}=0.07$ [$-$0.34, 0.47]). $n$ = total per model. All 37 models are fully stable ($\qopname  \relax m{min}(n_D,n_N)\geq 30$). \textbf  {Methodology note:} Effect sizes use population SD of the pooled D$+$N sample as denominator, which accounts for between-condition separation in the standardization (consistent with the cross-model table in \textsf  {lme\_report.md}). Confirmatory LME fixed-effect estimates ($\hat  {\beta }_D=0.179$, $\hat  {\beta }_C=0.243$; Table\nobreakspace  {}IV\hbox {}) provide the primary per-condition effect estimates controlling for persona and scenario random effects.}}{9}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:multimodel}{{VII}{9}}
